Thanks for helping develop the next generation of Niagara web applications!

The grunt-niagara plugin is configured to do several things: lint your files,
run unit tests, and generate docs.

Here are the available tasks:
{{#if eslint}}
grunt eslint: lint all files
                eslint:src - output results to screen
                eslint:ci - output results to a JUnit XML file{{/if}}{{#if karma}}
grunt karma:  do a single test run in Karma using PhantomJS{{/if}}{{#if jsdoc}}
grunt jsdoc:  generate JSDocs{{/if}}{{#if watch}}
grunt watch:  spin up in background and run {{#if eslint}}ESLint{{/if}}{{#if karma}} and Karma{{/if}} tests
              whenever a file changes{{/if}}
grunt ci:     perform continuous integration tasks

grunt flags:  print a list of available configuration flags
